Put a large #saucepan{} of water with @salt{0.5%tsp} on to boil for the pasta.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @echalion shallot{1}. Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Trim the @courgette{1}. Use a #peeler{} to peel long ribbons down the length of the courgette, stopping at the spongy centre.

Zest and halve the @lemon{0.5}(zested, juiced).

Once boiling, add the @rigatoni pasta{180%g} to the water and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

When ready, reserve some of the pasta water (about @reserved pasta water{100%ml}), then drain in a #colander{}.

Pop the pasta back into the #pan{}, drizzle with @oil{drizzle} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on medium heat. Once hot, add the courgette ribbons and season with @salt and @pepper. Cook until softened, ~{2-3%minutes}, then stir in the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Add the @baby spinach{100%g} a handful at a time and cook until wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}. Transfer everything to a large #bowl{} and cover to keep warm.

Put your (now empty) frying pan back on medium heat with a drizzle of @oil{drizzle}.

Once the oil is hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{240%g} and shallot and cook, stirring occasionally, until softened, ~{5-6%minutes}. Stir in the @vegetable stock paste{10%g} and reserved pasta water, then simmer until reduced by half, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Mix in the @creme fraiche{150%g} and heat through until piping hot, then season with @pepper.

Stir three quarters of the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g} through your creamy sauce.

Add the cooked pasta and half the cooked green veg and stir well to combine. Simmer until everything's piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add a pinch of lemon zest and a squeeze of lemon juice. Taste and add more salt, pepper and lemon juice if needed. Add a splash of water if it's a little too thick.

Share the creamy pasta between your bowls and top with the remaining cooked green veg.

Sprinkle over the remaining hard Italian style cheese and @toasted flaked almonds{15%g} to finish.

Enjoy!

> Step 4 MOD: If you're adding chicken, add it to the pan with the shallot. Fry for 5-6 mins instead, the chicken will cook through while simmering. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.